category: CHAMP CHANGE
category comment: 

clue: An Olympic award changes a letter & becomes this lever

response: a pedal (from medal)

clue: A 4-games-to-0 result in the World Series changes its second letter to "T" & becomes this adjective

response: steep (from sweep)

clue: Satisfaction taken in winning trades a "D" for a "Z" & becomes this award for winning

response: prize (from pride)

clue: A championship flag trades one of its "N"s for a "D" & becomes this dangling thing

response: pendant (from pennant)

clue: A verb meaning to admit, as into a hall of fame, changes a letter & becomes this verb meaning to infer from reasoning

response: induce (from induct)

